Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add @riced cauliflower{6%ounce} and garlic; season with half the @blackening spice{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. (You'll use the remaining Blackening Spice in the next step.) Cook, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @water{1/4%cup} and half the @chicken stock concentrate{2}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cauliflower is tender and liquid has cooked off, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with remaining Blackening Spice, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Remove from pan and set aside to rest.

Heat same pan over medium-high heat. Add @water{1/4%cup}, remaining stock concentrates, and a squeeze of lemon juice; cook until liquid has mostly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of lemon zest. Stir until butter melts. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Return pan with cauliflower grits to medium heat; stir in @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, and @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted and fully incorporated. Season generously with salt and pepper to taste.

> You'll use the remaining Blackening Spice in the next step.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide green beans and cauliflower grits between plates. Top cauliflower grits with blackened chicken. Drizzle pan sauce over chicken and serve.